	<div class="posts">
	<a name="114227643164630672"></a>
    
    <h2><font color="#000080"><!-- 2004-08-31 -->
    
    Orcmid's Lair: Global Social Identity
    
    </font></h2>
    
    
    <p>
	<div style="clear:both;"></div><p><a href="http://nfocentrale.net/orcmid/blog/2006/03/global-social-identity.asp">Orcmid's Lair: Global Social Identity</a>.&nbsp; This is an Orcmid&rsquo;s Lair blog.&nbsp; I&rsquo;m using the same ClustrMap&nbsp;here on Clueless because I&rsquo;m interested in&nbsp;an aggregate profile, not one by individual blog (or individual posts).</p><p>This does not account for all of the traffic, because there are other places visited on the site beside the blogs.&nbsp;&nbsp;My logs tell me that there is an interesting spread of interests in particular pages, so it would be interesting to catch those visits as I perform site refreshs and page updates from time to time.</p><p align="center">{tags: <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/orcmid" rel="tag">orcmid</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/orcmid" rel="tag">identity</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/site+statistics" rel="tag">site statistics</a>}</p><hr><small><p>This post is&nbsp;yet-another&nbsp;pretense for pushing the&nbsp;blog template&nbsp;with ClustrMap image and link out to my main page.&nbsp;&nbsp; I&rsquo;m working on other posts that would accomplish that, but I don&rsquo;t want to wait seeing how this works.&nbsp; One oddity is the suggestion that it is visits to a page (rather than all pages having the image) that is being tallied.&nbsp; An interesting coherence shear case, that.</p></small><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom: 0.25em;"></div>
    </p>
	<span class="byline">posted by orcmid
       at <a href="http://orcmid.com/BlunderDome/clueless/2006/03/orcmids-lair-global-social-identity.asp">3/13/2006 11:00:31 AM</a>,
